Ad Text:
We're seeking two experienced Senior Business Analysts to join a major transformation program within the mortgage domain. This is a multi-year initiative focused on simplifying processes, improving customer experience, and driving operational efficiency across large-scale systems and business change.


The Roles

You'll work as part of a high-performing delivery team responsible for analysing complex mortgage systems, defining business requirements, and enabling strategic change. One role will focus on system uplift, while the other will lead migration activities from the ground up.


Key Responsibilities
Elicit, analyse, document, and manage detailed business and system requirements

Partner with stakeholders to define and deliver solutions that achieve strategic business outcomes

Conduct detailed gap analyses between current and target states

Use data analysis to validate requirements and identify data quality issues or business scenarios

Support design, evaluation, and implementation of solutions across complex programs

Identify risks and ensure alignment with governance and delivery frameworks

What You'll Bring
Proven experience as a senior business analyst in large, complex financial or technology programs

Deep understanding of mortgage systems, products, and processes

Demonstrated experience in customer or data migration programs

Strong analytical mindset and structured problem-solving approach

Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills

Ability to work autonomously and collaboratively within fast-paced delivery teams

Contract Details
Duration: 12 months, with extensions likely on a 4-year program

Location: Sydney CBD - 2 days in office


If the above looks of interest please make an application and Manpower will be in contact with you.


Talent Solutions as part of ManpowerGroup is committed to being a Diversity Confident Recruiter and encourages applications from people from a diverse range of backgrounds, including people with a disability. Please indicate your preferred method of communication in your resume and please let us know if you require any reasonable adjustments should you be contacted for an interview.

Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people are encouraged to apply.

Ad Text:
Company Description

KPMG are a leading consulting firm specialising in enterprise performance management and analytics solutions. Our mission is to help organisations make smarter, data-driven decisions through innovative planning and forecasting systems. We work with government agencies and major corporations, delivering solutions that transform financial and operational planning processes.

Job Description

We are seeking a Manager to design, build and support advanced planning and reporting solutions for our clients using IBM Planning Analytics (TM1). This client-facing role focuses on delivering high-quality budgeting, planning and forecasting models that enable better business decisions.

The successful candidate will have strong Planning Analytics skills and ideally will come from a combination of financial management and TM1 technical experience. 

Key Responsibilities

Design, develop, and implement IBM Planning Analytics (TM1) models for budgeting, planning, and forecasting.

Engage directly with clients to gather requirements and translate them into robust solutions.

Optimise and maintain TM1 applications for performance and scalability.

Provide technical support and troubleshooting for client environments.

Collaborate with stakeholders to ensure solutions align with business objectives.

Lead minor engagements, contribute to best practices, and mentor junior team members as you grow in your leadership role.

Some travel to client sites may be required.

How you are Extraordinary? 

Through your work experience and knowledge in Finance/ Accounting, built over a 5 year period, you have acquired some of the following skills and capabilities: 

Strong understanding of budgeting, planning, and forecasting processes.

Excellent client-facing written and verbal communication and stakeholder management skills.

Consulting experience (optional but highly regarded).

Project Management experience (optional and well regard).

Expertise in IBM Planning Analytics/TM1 (PAW, PAfE, TurboIntegrator, Rules).

Experience with SQL, Python, or MDX.

Strong skills in financial modelling, variance analysis, and management reporting.

Advanced spreadsheet, data management, and reporting or visualisation tool skills.

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification in Accounting, Finance, or a related discipline.

Australian citizen with current or eligible Australian Government security clearance (we will sponsor clearance).

IBM Planning Analytics certification.

Additional Information

KPMG is a professional services firm with global outreach and deep sector experience. We work with clients across an array of industries to solve complex challenges, steer change and enable growth. 

Our people are what make KPMG the thriving workplace that it is and what sets us apart is that we know great minds think differently. Collaborate with a team of passionate, highly skilled professionals who’ve got your back. You’ll build relationships with unique and diverse colleagues who will provide you with the support you need to be your best and produce meaningful and impactful work in an inclusive, equitable culture.

At KPMG, you’ll take control over how you work. We’re embracing a new way of working in many ways, from offering flexible hours and locations to generous paid parental leave and career breaks. Our people enjoy a variety of exciting perks, including retail discounts, health and wellbeing initiatives, learning and growth opportunities, salary packaging options and more.

Diverse candidates have diverse needs. During your recruitment journey, information will be provided about adjustment requests. If you require additional support before submitting your application, please contact the Talent Attraction Support Team.

At KPMG every career is different, and we look forward to seeing how you grow with us.

Brighter Futures Start Here

We are an inclusive team who power two of the most iconic and loved brands, Kmart and Target. We have more than 50,000 passionate individuals across our stores, distribution centres, and offices around the globe.

With our brands touching the lives of almost two million customers every week, you'll feel the impact of the work you'll do every day. As a leader in the retail market, we're optimistic about our future and yours. We're changing at a rapid rate, giving you challenging work that you'll be proud of.

We're excited to share that our team will be moving to our new Chadstone office in early 2026!
This will be a space that brings us together — inspiring creativity, collaboration, and connection as we embark on this exciting new chapter.

Join the team



We are seeking an Analytics Lead to define, deliver and drive adoption of end-to-end analytics solutions that create strategic business value. Reporting to the Senior Manager - Advanced Analytics, you will partner with business stakeholders, technology teams, data engineers and scientists to scope, develop and deliver advanced analytics solutions into production.

This is a hands-on role with an initial focus on Online fulfilment, where you'll translate business challenges into technical solutions, ensuring our data products are fit-for-purpose and drive measurable outcomes across our supply chain.



Applications close January 11th 2026. Applications will be reviewed after the closure date.



What you'll be doing


Building strong partnerships with business stakeholders and analytics teams.
Conducting exploratory data analysis to diagnose problems and produce actionable insights.
Leading implementation and adoption of analytics solutions from pilot to scale.
Translating business needs into technical requirements for data scientists and engineers.
Synthesising complex outputs into clear, actionable recommendations for business leaders.
Driving measurable value through use cases and analytical products.
Training users, running experiments, and refining models over time.
Communicating progress, risks, and outcomes effectively to stakeholders.


To be successful in this role you'll have:



Bachelor's degree in Business, Engineering, Science, Finance, Economics or Statistics, or another relevant field.
5-7 years' experience in analytics translation, product ownership, consulting, or data science/ML solutions.
Strong skills in SQL and visualisation tools such as Power BI or Snowflake.
Experience in Agile methodology and product management tooling.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with strong attention to detail.
Outstanding communication skills and ability to collaborate across diverse teams.
A commercial mindset and ability to influence stakeholders.

Benefits we'll offer you:

Flexible hybrid working options through our Flex Where, Flex When, Flex Well policy.
A team member discount card that gives you a discount at Kmart, Target, Officeworks and Bunnings
Access to the Kmart for You benefits program which entitles you to exclusive discounts and benefits in the areas of entertainment, travel, lifestyle, and health - with over 60 suppliers!
We want you to feel rewarded for your commitment and hard work that's why eligible team members get the opportunity to participate in a bonus program
We offer inclusive parental leave, and ongoing support offered though our partnership with Circle In for team members of all backgrounds and family circumstances
A dynamic learning and support program
Opportunity to fast track your career through our Mentor Program as a Mentee or Mentor
A Kudos recognition program, where you are nominated by your peers to spin a wheel, to win a stack of cool prizes
Great career opportunities across the broader Wesfarmers Group


We celebrate the rich diversity of the communities in which we operate. We are committed to creating inclusive and safe environments where all our team members can contribute and succeed. We believe that all team members should feel valued, respected and safe, and strive to ensure our recruitment process is accessible and welcoming, with applications encouraged from all candidates.

We encourage you to tell us about any workplace adjustments that you would like, by emailing kmartgroupcareers@kmart.com.au.

If you would like to explore a career with Kmart and this sounds like the perfect role for you - apply now!

Job Title: Associate Director - Finance Advisory, Risk Consulting
Salary: Our people build skills for the future
Ad Text:
Company Description

KPMG Australia is part of a global network providing extensive services across a wide range of industries and sectors. Our people collaborate, share their expertise and create innovation as we partner with clients to solve complex challenges, empower change, and drive disruption and growth.

Working in the Consulting division, KPMG's Finance Advisory team partner with CFO's, program and portfolio managers and finance transformation leaders to deliver efficient and effective finance functions.

Join a market-leading team at KPMG Australia , where we collaborate with Australia’s largest government and public sector clients to deliver strategic financial advisory and transformation services. Our multidisciplinary team combines deep expertise in financial control, costing, reporting, and commercial advisory to help clients navigate complex challenges and achieve their strategic goals.

Job Description

Your Opportunity

As an Associate Director,  you will play a pivotal role in delivering high-impact financial and commercial advisory services across multiple engagements within Defence and other Federal Government Departments. You’ll work across a variety of projects and closely with capable individuals and stakeholders to perform a range of activities such as:

Cost estimation: primarily for Defence capability, working with projects and service groups to shape project documents for internal Defence and Cabinet approvals (gates 0 to 2).

Cost assurance: Verify the integrity of existing estimates and forecasts and provide insight into the broader outcomes at the program or domain levels.

Financial Modelling: Construct and refresh financial models of project lifecycle cost estimates.

Financial Data Analytics: Use data-driven insights to support decision-making and performance improvement.

Procurement & Commercial Advisory: Advise on financial aspects of procurement strategies and value-for-money assessments.

Business case and investment analysis: resource costing to operationalise new policies, cost allocation and financial analysis, and developing funding and investment strategies to inform critical decisions.

Your Experience

At KPMG, we value diversity of thought, background and experience. Our ideal candidate will bring: 

Demonstrated experience in financial advisory, costing, or transformation roles within Defence, government or consulting environments.

Proficiency in financial modelling tools and Microsoft Excel

Ability to manage multiple projects and deliver high-quality outcomes

Expertise in interpreting complex financial standards and frameworks

A thorough understanding of the Defence environment and the capability lifecycle (and preferably familiarity with the Capability Cost Template).

Excellent communication, presentation, and stakeholder engagement skills

Strong analytical and commercial mindset 

Qualifications

Tertiary qualifications in accounting, finance, actuarial, business, engineering or related fields. Professional certifications such as CA, CPA, CIMA or CPEng are highly regarded.

Additional Information

To be considered for this role, candidates must be Australian Citizens and hold an active government security clearance

DXC Technology (NYSE:DXC) - where brilliant people embrace change and seize opportunities to advance their careers and amplify customer success. People are the heart of our business.

DXC Technology’s Practice for Oracle is the largest independent provider of Oracle consulting and managed services in Australia and New Zealand.

We are seeking a seasoned Principal Oracle SCM Consultant to lead strategic initiatives across our Oracle ERP customer base. As a Principal Consultant, you will be responsible for delivering end-to-end world class solutions, from initial requirements gathering to post go-live support, including functional designs for reports and integrations. You should be confident in customer facing roles and will be expected to deliver presentations eloquently.

Must Have Requirements

10+ years of hands-on Oracle ERP experience, with at least 3 years in a principal or lead role.
Proven track record of delivering large-scale ERP implementations and enhancements.
Experience managing teams and working in matrixed environments.
Excellent communication, leadership, and stakeholder management skills.
Key Responsibilities

ERP Strategy & Leadership
Lead the functional design and delivery of Oracle solutions across SCM and touch points with Financials and Projects.
Serve as the ERP subject matter expert, guiding enterprise-wide decisions and roadmap planning.
Manage cross-functional teams including internal staff, vendors, and consultants.
Functional Design & Solution Architecture
Design and document functional specifications for custom components including:
Integrations (e.g., with third-party systems, legacy applications, cloud services)
Reports (BI Publisher, OTBI, custom dashboards)
Collaborate with technical teams to ensure alignment between functional requirements and technical implementation.
Project Management & Delivery
Oversee end-to-end ERP implementations, upgrades, and enhancements.
Work with project managers to develop project plans, manage budgets, and ensure timely delivery of milestones.
Facilitate UAT, training, and change management activities.
Stakeholder Engagement
Partner with Finance, HR, Supply Chain, and other business units to understand needs and translate them into ERP solutions.
Communicate effectively with executive leadership, providing insights and recommendations.
In alignment with our commitment to fostering a flexible and dynamic work environment, we have adopted a hybrid working approach that acknowledges the importance of in-person collaboration while recognising that the determination of your work location will be based on a range of factors to ensure both individual preferences and operational requirements are met.
  
If you would like to be part of a culture that drives innovation, delivers results, rewards performance and encourages ideas, then please press the "Apply Now" button to submit your resume.

This is an excellent opportunity for an energetic, dynamic Senior Commercial Analyst to join a successful, global construction group.

Reporting into the CFO you'll act as a business partner to operational stakeholders, providing commercial, financial & analytical support, to help drive decisions & business performance.

Your analytical scope will encompass areas such as category sales, discounting, gross margins, pre & post promotional analysis and wages. You'll create financial models in order to provide meaningful insights into business performance issues, challenging decisions where necessary.

You'll also prepare and distribute weekly & monthly reports, with associated commentary, for use by the business. And will hold regular meetings with Category Managers and the Commercial Director, to review monthly sales, margin results etc.

Additionally, you'll play a key role in business planning for new stores, budgeting, forecasting and other ad hoc analysis when required.

You are an experienced Financial or Commercial Analyst - who will be ready to step into a Commercial Manager role in the next 1-2 years. Circa 5 years experience in Commercial Finance role/s would be ideal.

You'll have proven analytical skills, combined with a background in business partnering. You will also have advanced Excel / modelling skills, whilst experience using a BI tool and working with large data sets.

For more information, please contact Schenuk Wijesekera on 02 9775 5916. Or to apply, hit the "apply" button.

The opportunity

This is an excellent opportunity for an energetic, dynamic Commercial Analyst to join a successful, Aussie company. ASX listed.

Reporting into the Commercial Manager you'll act as a business partner to operational stakeholders, providing commercial, financial & analytical support, to help drive decisions & business performance.

Your remit will include budgeting, forecasting, P&L review, financial modelling and commercial analysis, providing commercial support to department heads, monitoring key performance metrics and other ad hoc analysis.

About you

This role is an excellent role for a Financial Analyst with <3 years experience, or a Financial/Management Accountant with some budgeting/forecasting experience to take on this highly analytical role which will be hands on with implementing and driving change across this large corporate. Strong excel and BI skills is highly regarded.

For more information, please contact Schenuk Wijesekera on 02 9775 5916. Or to apply, hit the "apply" button.

Company: Little Company of Mary Health Care
Ad Text:
Progress with purpose at one of Australia’s largest health care providers
Get ahead with salary packaging, benefits and professional development in a supportive team environment
Join a dynamic project team where your expertise in providing clear and insightful models for private hospital revenue and costings will be prized
Flexible Location: Melbourne, Sydney, Adelaide.
 
About the role
 
We are recruiting for a Senior Data Scientist with 5+ years in a healthcare data science role and demonstrated experience in either private hospital revenue or costings. The role will start with a project focused on private hospital modelling but play a core role in building our ML/AI Engineering over the next 3 years.

Hybrid office with team across Melbourne, Sydney and Adelaide. Applicants from ACT will also be considered.

Your main duties will include:
Design, develop and maintain models to support private hospital costing and revenue projects. This will extend to supporting projects more broadly across hospitals, aged and home care over time.
Define opportunities for predictive modelling projects and design, develop and maintain approved solutions.
Collaborate with operational, finance and strategy teams to deliver actionable insights that improve quality of service, safety and operational sustainability.
 
About you
Proven experience in private hospital revenue modelling or hospital costings and deep understanding of Australian healthcare funding models
Experience of using advanced analytics, data mining, statistical modelling and machine-learning techniques
Ability to model different scenarios, and to communicate how variations in independent variables could affect the final outcome
Ability to communicate complex analytical findings to non-technical stakeholders.
For further information please contact Michael Bishop, Head of Data, Insights & Analytics at michael.bishop@calvarycare.org.au
 
 
Why work for Calvary?
 
At Calvary, our staff matter. 
 
With over 130 years’ experience and 18,000 staff and volunteers, we offer an inclusive and welcoming culture where you are valued, drawing on your own strengths, identity and background alongside a team of professionals who care for our patients, residents and clients.
 
Your benefits: 
NFP salary packaging benefits, discounted health insurance and gym memberships 
Paid parental leave 
Training, development pathways and career opportunities
Flexible hours that make sense for you
As we serve the community across Home, Virtual and Residential Aged Care, Retirement Living and Hospitals, one thing sets us apart. Care from the heart. If this sounds like you, apply for a role with Calvary today.
 
Please note the following:
As part of the application process, you will be required to complete pre-employment checks which may include, but is not limited to reference checks, work rights, criminal history check, NDIS/WWCC/WWVP checks, and a health evaluation to ensure suitability for the role

Hewitt – the most influential & trusted provider of high claims organic protein

Hewitt is on a mission to become the most trusted and influential supplier of organic, high-claims animal proteins. With a commitment to unrivalled quality and consistency, we serve customers and consumers in over seven countries through a vertically integrated global supply chain—from farm to plate. We proudly support the growing demand for nutritious, sustainable, and high-quality red meat.

Our purpose is simple: “To feed the world with a system that lasts forever.”

With a rich family history spanning over 120 years, the Hewitt family has always been dedicated to sustainable agriculture. Guided by the simple philosophy of ‘treat the land well, treat people well, and treat animals well’, the company has grown from its humble beginnings as a beef cattle farm in central Queensland, into a global business. Today, brothers Mick and Ben Hewitt lead the vision and development of supplying market leading organic and high-claims products that meet the demanding specifications of large, fast-paced supermarket retail chains, foodservice operators and wholesalers.

We champion regenerative organic agriculture, passionately commit to animal welfare, actively support the communities we serve, and lead the world in biodiversity and carbon management practices. For decades, Hewitt has proudly supplied many of the world’s largest food wholesalers and retailers, earning numerous industry awards and recognitions for our efforts.

Our retail brand portfolio includes Cleaver’s Organic Meat, the most trusted organic meat brand in Australia.

The Opportunity (3-month contract, with possibility for extension)
This is a pivotal role that shapes strategic direction and influences high-impact decisions. As our Business & ERP Analyst, you will evaluate current operations, identify opportunities for improvement, and deliver business requirements that enhance efficiency and effectiveness across the organisation. . The successful candidate will collaborate with senior leaders and teams across Finance, Primary, Manufacturing, and Livestock Management, bringing a process focused mindset, strong communication skills, and a passion for process improvement within the food processing sector.

You will collaborate closely with senior leaders and cross-functional teams to drive process improvement initiatives and contribute to the evolution of our ERP landscape.

Key Responsibilities:

Business Process Analysis & Requirements Gathering

Analyse current workflows, identify gaps, and define future-state processes aligned with ERP capabilities.

Gather requirements through interviews, workshops, and observation.

Develop Business Requirement Documents (BRDs), Functional Requirement Documents (FRDs), and use cases.

Align requirements with APQC Process Framework.

Prepare findings and recommendations for stakeholders across all levels.

ERP Functional Knowledge & Data Awareness

Apply ERP functional knowledge to requirements and process mapping.

Analyse data flows between ERP and other systems to ensure data consistency and integration.

Evaluate ERP vendor solutions against requirements and assist in the RFP process.

Stakeholder Engagement

Collaborate with department leads, end-users, and technical teams to validate requirements and manage expectations.

Support stakeholder engagement and obtain sign-off for requirements.

Contribute to training materials and adoption strategies.

Candidate Requirements:

Strong understanding of ERP systems and core modules (Finance, Supply Chain, Manufacturing, HR).

Proven experience in requirements gathering, documentation, and process improvement.

Knowledge of data flows, master data management, and system integrations.

Proficiency in process modelling tools such as Visio or Lucidchart.

Excellent communication, stakeholder management, analytical, and problem-solving skills.

Familiarity with Tier One ERP platforms.

Bachelor’s degree in Business, IT, or a related field; ERP certification is a plus.

Why Join Us:

Make a tangible impact on business performance and operational resilience.

Work with a collaborative and high-performing team across multiple business areas.

Opportunity to drive change and innovation in a dynamic food processing environment.

About the RACP 
The Royal Australasian College of Physicians (RACP) connects, represents, and trains physicians and trainee physicians across Australia and Aotearoa New Zealand. The RACP provides services to support the delivery of training, continuing professional development, and health policy and advocacy to medical health professionals. 

Our Values 
Accountable | Collaborate | Indigenise and Decolonise | Lead the way | Respect 

Why Join Us? 
As part of our team, you will be offered a competitive remuneration salary and access to some amazing benefits including a flexible hybrid work model, additional paid leave between Christmas and New Year, paid parental leave, free annual flu vaccinations, professional development opportunities, access to our Employee Assistance Program, special corporate discounts and more! To view all our benefits, visit www.racp.edu.au/about/careers-at-racp.

Our 3-2-1 Hybrid Working Model

3 days from anywhere in Australia or Aotearoa New Zealand per week,  
2 days from an RACP office location per week,  
1 of the two days per week in office spent with your team.  



The RACP is undertaking a significant transformation program which is designed to enhance member value, modernise core systems, and build the digital and data capabilities needed to thrive in a changing health and education landscape. The Program's key goals are to significantly improve member satisfaction, employee experience, and reduce cost to serve.

This role is part of the Program TRELLIS team which is responsible for the Implementation of a solution that underpins the delivery of improved employee and member experience “the north star” via new technology and new/improved processes.  The Senior BA works closely with the Product Owner, suppliers and employees to ensure they have an in-depth understanding of the current state, the proposed solution, acceptance criteria and change impacts to existing/new processes.

Liaise with business stakeholders and technical teams (including vendors)

Ability to critically analyse issues and problems and propose innovative and fit for purpose solutions aligned with strategic and business priorities
Ability to re-exam existing practices and processes, generating new ideas and implementing improvements

Detail oriented, decisive and goal oriented with a strong ability to adapt plans to meet changes in landscape. 

Desired

Experience of the RACP or a similar organisation

At Intelligen, we’re building something different. Over the past three years, we’ve evolved from a bold startup to a trusted partner for some of Australia’s most complex data transformations. We’ve helped organisations move from legacy to modern platforms, embedded governance into decision-making, and brought AI into the hands of the business - responsibly and at speed.

But we’re just getting started. As we move into our next phase of growth, we’re looking for consultants who don’t just want to deliver great solutions - but help shape the future of data and AI capability across Australia.

About the Opportunity...

We’re looking for a Data Engineer, based in Melbourne, who can design and deliver modern, scalable data solutions across multi-cloud environments (AWS, GCP, Azure) and modern data stacks such as Databricks, Snowflake, dbt, and cloud-native services.

You’ll work directly with clients to understand their data challenges, architect and build high-quality pipelines, and support analytics, governance, and AI enablement initiatives. This role blends hands-on engineering with consulting - helping clients realise value at pace while contributing to Intelligen’s growing engineering capability.

This role is ideal for someone who loves solving complex engineering problems, thrives in modern data ecosystems, and wants to work in a high-performing team doing meaningful, future-shaping work.

What You’ll Do

Design, build, and optimise scalable, reliable data pipelines across cloud platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure)
Work with modern data technologies such as Databricks, Snowflake, cloud data lakes, and orchestration tools
Develop high-quality data models to support analytics, reporting, and AI use cases
Collaborate with clients to translate business requirements into well-structured, actionable data solutions
Implement data ingestion, transformation, storage, and access layers across multi-cloud environments
Support or implement dbt, CI/CD, and engineering best practices across projects
Ensure strong data quality, governance, lineage, and performance practices
Contribute to reusable components, accelerators, and internal engineering frameworks
Work closely with cross-functional consultants, analysts, and architects to deliver cohesive solutions
Mentor junior engineers and positively influence client delivery

What You’ll Bring

Curiosity and a problem-solving mindset. You enjoy understanding how things work and making them better.
A commitment to clean, scalable engineering practices and continuous learning
A collaborative spirit. You enjoy working across teams to deliver real outcomes.The confidence to share ideas, challenge the norm, and help build something better.


Requirements


4–6+ years’ experience in data engineering or analytics engineering
Strong hands-on experience with Databricks, and at least one major cloud platform (AWS, GCP, or Azure)
Solid SQL capability and experience building complex data transformations
Familiarity with modern data stacks - e.g., Snowflake, dbt, Delta Lake, cloud ETL/orchestration tools
Experience working across the full data lifecycle: ingestion → transformation → modelling → consumption
Consulting, stakeholder-facing experience, or cross-functional delivery exposure
Knowledge of DevOps concepts, version control, and/or CI/CD in data environments
Excellent communication, problem-solving, and collaboration skills
Melbourne-based, with ability to work on-site with clients as required
A mindset of curiosity, delivery excellence, and continuous learning


Benefits



We’re not just delivering AI and data projects, we’re humanising them. That means we care deeply about the how, not just the what. We value curiosity, creativity, and a willingness to challenge the status quo. We look for people who are driven to build a business, get curious, and offer up their opinions and ideas.

As well as:

Work From Home - Flexible hours
Training & Development
Free Food & Snacks
Many socials and community groups
Opportunity to drive projects that are of interest to you!

You’ll work with a team that’s smart, kind, and ambitious. You’ll have real influence in your projects, your practice, and our business. And as we grow, so will you.

Job Title: Senior Manager, AI Strategy and Innovation
Ad Text:
Melbourne, Victoria | RACV Head Office

Permanent, Full Time | Hybrid Working

A Competitive Salary | Discounts on Selected RACV Products




Great things start here

Join our team of business professionals doing meaningful work in an organisation that’s ever evolving. Work with people who care and expand your career with opportunities only a diverse business can provide. With license to see things through your way, and the option to split your time between office and home, RACV is where you’ll make a difference.




About the Opportunity

The Senior Manager, AI Strategy is a pivotal role responsible for shaping RACV’s AI direction by proactively identifying new AI opportunities, shaping the forward macro-programme and ensuring RACV’s AI agenda is market leading.

This role demands gravitas and a strong consulting background, ideally gained within a leading consultancy, to drive strategic initiatives, scan external trends, and guide annual AI reviews. You will produce insight-driven content including market vignettes and case studies, embedding strategic thinking across the enterprise.




Come along for a new journey

You’ll be instrumental in ensuring our AI team delivers exceptional service. Here’s a glimpse of what you’ll be doing:

External AI View:
Continuously monitor and analyse external AI market, competitor, and industry developments to guide RACV’s AI strategic direction.

Enterprise AI Roadmap Development:
Lead the strategy and insights work underpinning the creation and evolution of the enterprise AI roadmap, ensuring alignment with internal capabilities and external trends.

Opportunity Identification & Sizing:
Proactively identify, assess, and size new AI opportunities by analysing internal business needs and external market, competitor, and technology trends.

Initiative Shaping & Value Articulation:
Shape and prioritise AI-based initiatives and use cases, clearly articulating their value to RACV and collaborating with business stakeholders to agree on potential benefits.

Experimentation & Approach Recommendation:
Propose initial approaches (build or buy) for new initiatives, emphasising the importance of experimentation to validate concepts and inform investment decisions.

Stakeholder Engagement & Collaboration:
Work closely with Product Owners, business SMEs, and experimentation teams to ensure AI initiatives are relevant, feasible, and aligned with business objectives

 


What you’ll need to be successful

 Must have a minimum of 5+ years’ experience in strategy consulting.

Additional background in advanced analytics, data science, or AI-focused roles is highly advantageous

Demonstrated ability to develop and execute strategy with a strong external focus, leveraging market, competitor, and industry insights to inform organizational direction. 

Proven track record in advising, designing, and implementing data-driven strategies that deliver measurable business value. 

Strong engagement, communication, and influencing skills, with experience presenting to and collaborating with senior management (EGMs/CEO) and cross-functional teams. 

Effective matrix leadership and collaboration skills, driving alignment and adoption of AI strategy across diverse business units. 

Experience leading change and fostering a culture of innovation in complex organizational environments




There’s so much on offer when you join RACV with benefits including

Our flexible and informal work environment which helps bring balance between work and home.

Generous discounts on home and car insurance policies and RACV roadside care

Great discounts across all RACV resorts

Discounts from corporate partners that are updated monthly.




Our difference

We want our people to feel welcome, supported and appreciated for who they are and what they bring to our business. If you require any reasonable adjustments to the recruitment process and/or the role, please let our Talent Acquisition Team know.

Job Title: Data Business Analyst | Data Management & Governance
Ad Text:
Our Data and AI team within the Operations division is dedicated to maximising the value of data across Macquarie. We bring together diverse expertise to govern and manage data, ensuring it supports business objectives, enhances operational efficiency, and mitigates risk for the organisation.


At Macquarie, our advantage is bringing together diverse people and empowering them to shape all kinds of possibilities. We are a global financial services group operating in 31 markets and with 56 years of unbroken profitability. You’ll be part of a friendly and supportive team where everyone - no matter what role - contributes ideas and drives outcomes.


What role will you play?
As a Data Business Analyst, you will play a pivotal role in strengthening trust in our data through effective governance and management practices. You will collaborate with stakeholders across the business to define, manage, and improve data quality, while coaching others in best practice data management. Your work will help ensure our data is ready for advanced analytics and AI, supporting the delivery of measurable business outcomes.


What you offer
Strong data business analyst skills including relationship-building skills with the ability to understand stakeholder requirements, communicate effectively, and partner to deliver outcomes
Experience managing data and applying data governance practices, ideally within financial services or a related sector
Proficiency with data management tools and platforms, such as Collibra, and familiarity with data analysis tools including SQL, Dataiku, Alteryx, and PowerBI
A track record of delivering measurable business improvements through data governance and management activities, with a customer-focused approach and the ability to manage multiple priorities
Excellent analytical and communication skills, adaptability to change, and an interest in emerging technologies such as Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning.
We love hearing from anyone inspired to build a better future with us, if you're excited about the role or working at Macquarie we encourage you to apply.


What we offer
At Macquarie, you’re empowered to shape a career that’s rewarding in all the ways that matter most to you. Macquarie employees can access a wide range of benefits which, depending on employment type, include:
1 wellbeing leave day per year
Up to 5 additional service bonus leave days per year
Up to 20 weeks’ paid parental leave for primary caregivers along with 12 days of transition leave upon return to work, and 6 weeks’ paid leave for non-primary caregivers
2 days of paid volunteer leave and donation matching
Up to 12 months’ gender affirmation leave, including 6 weeks’ paid leave
Access to Employee Assistance Program and wellbeing benefits including skin and health checks, and flu vaccinations
Access to a wide range of salary packaging options
Access to a wide range of learning and development opportunities, including reimbursement for professional membership or subscription
Hybrid and flexible working arrangements, dependent on role
Reimbursement for work from home equipment


About Corporate Operations Group
In our Corporate Operations Group, you will work at the heart of Macquarie to deliver for our people, businesses, and their customers. We’re a global, collaborative team with deep expertise in technology, data, digital, market operations, corporate real estate, business resilience, procurement and global security.


Our commitment to diversity, equity and inclusion
We are committed to fostering a diverse, equitable and inclusive workplace. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and welcome all identities, including race, ethnicity, cultural identity, nationality, gender (including gender identity or expression), age, sexual orientation, marital or partnership status, parental, caregiving or family status, family and domestic violence status, neurodiversity, religion or belief, disability, or socio-economic background.
